WEBVTT

00:02.120 --> 00:03.838
HANK: Erstwhile on Fargo...

00:03.920 --> 00:06.594
You're not gonna prove
my Ed did anything wrong.

00:06.680 --> 00:07.795
It's unprovable!

00:07.920 --> 00:10.116
<i>LOU: There was a cleaver
in the man's head, son,</i>

00:10.200 --> 00:11.713
which Noreen said was you.

00:11.800 --> 00:13.313
Not to mention
there's a war going on

00:13.400 --> 00:14.629
up in Fargo that
you may have started

00:14.720 --> 00:16.040
when you ran over
that Gerhardt boy.

00:17.240 --> 00:18.275
FLOYD:
Take care of this butcher.

00:18.440 --> 00:19.635
He doesn't live
through the night.

00:19.760 --> 00:21.910
Already dead, believe me.
He just doesn't know it.

00:22.760 --> 00:24.751
PEGGY: Sheriff?
HANK: Go inside now, Peggy.

00:25.120 --> 00:26.269
Go now.

00:29.160 --> 00:30.719
Ed home?
Ed who?

00:31.560 --> 00:32.914
No, Peggy, hey, hey...

00:33.480 --> 00:34.470
(GRUNTS)

00:35.400 --> 00:38.472
When I find you, darling,
I'm gonna make you bleed.

00:45.840 --> 00:47.592
ED: I need to find Peggy.

00:47.680 --> 00:48.909
LOU: You're still
in my custody.

00:49.600 --> 00:51.591
You look worse than me.

00:51.760 --> 00:54.798
HANK: Don't tire yourself.
We know where he's headed.

01:16.880 --> 01:18.837
ED: Hon! Hon!

02:06.680 --> 02:07.829
MAN: Peggy?

02:13.720 --> 02:14.869
Peggy?

02:18.960 --> 02:20.997
Have you actualized fully?

02:25.720 --> 02:26.835
What?

02:27.320 --> 02:29.550
Have you actualized fully?

02:32.840 --> 02:34.956
I don't know.
(CLICKS TONGUE)

02:35.360 --> 02:37.237
I mean, I'm trying.

02:38.000 --> 02:40.116
Do you feel cold sometimes,

02:40.200 --> 02:41.349
even when it's hot?

02:42.440 --> 02:43.794
Sometimes.

02:46.400 --> 02:49.153
Do you understand
the difference between

02:49.240 --> 02:50.594
thinking and being?

02:53.440 --> 02:54.760
What do you mean?

02:54.840 --> 02:59.914
Do you understand the difference
between thinking and being?

03:02.440 --> 03:03.510
(SIGHS)

03:04.000 --> 03:04.990
I...

03:05.120 --> 03:07.589
To be,
is simply to exist.

03:09.280 --> 03:10.475
Try it.

03:11.560 --> 03:13.312
Try simply being.

03:22.320 --> 03:23.799
I'm sorry,

03:24.760 --> 03:29.277
but how is sitting here gonna help
me be the best person I can be?

03:29.560 --> 03:30.550
Ah.

03:30.640 --> 03:31.630
(CHUCKLES)

03:32.720 --> 03:34.677
You want an explanation.

03:35.920 --> 03:37.319
Well, kinda.

03:38.800 --> 03:43.317
The human mind, aroused by
an insistence for meaning,

03:43.480 --> 03:46.313
seeks and finds nothing

03:46.400 --> 03:47.595
but contradiction

03:47.680 --> 03:48.829
and nonsense.

03:52.240 --> 03:55.596
Okay. It's just...

03:55.680 --> 03:59.469
Practically, I'm saying,
as a person...

04:01.160 --> 04:03.913
A married person, a woman

04:04.000 --> 04:07.789
who's worried she's not
living up to her full potential.

04:08.880 --> 04:09.870
Hmm.

04:11.200 --> 04:13.032
Think or be.

04:17.120 --> 04:18.793
You can't do both.

04:22.160 --> 04:27.553
You're saying, "Don't think
about the person I wanna be,

04:27.640 --> 04:29.517
"just be that person."

04:30.880 --> 04:31.870
Peggy.

04:32.000 --> 04:35.914
Don't think about the person I
wanna be, just be that person.

04:36.600 --> 04:37.749
Just be that person.

04:37.880 --> 04:41.430
Peggy?
Peggy, are you okay?

04:41.520 --> 04:44.672
We were just talking, and
it all finally makes sense!

04:44.760 --> 04:46.239
This lady has lost
her mind, brother.

04:48.600 --> 04:50.432
Shut up. She's seeing
people who are not there.

04:50.560 --> 04:51.550
I said, shut up!

04:51.640 --> 04:52.994
DODD: Here I am tied
up for no reason.

04:53.080 --> 04:57.313
A concerned citizen just walking
past, and I hear a cry for help.

04:58.520 --> 04:59.794
No, you're a Gerhardt.

05:02.080 --> 05:03.479
And you're shit on my shoe.

05:03.560 --> 05:05.233
Why don't you come here,
let me wipe you off.

05:11.520 --> 05:12.510
(GRUNTS)

05:16.600 --> 05:19.479
Okay, are the cops coming?
Who knows who else.

05:19.560 --> 05:21.312
Okay, no time to pack.
Just the clothes on our back.

05:21.400 --> 05:23.073
Okay.
Okay? Okay.

05:25.760 --> 05:27.319
Did you...

05:28.080 --> 05:31.232
It was him.
He's the leader, I think.

05:34.040 --> 05:35.758
Then we take him with us.

05:36.920 --> 05:37.990
ED: Peg!

05:39.080 --> 05:40.832
PEGGY:
We're taking his car?

05:40.920 --> 05:42.718
ED: Yeah, they'll be
looking for ours.

05:43.080 --> 05:44.070
I understand now, hon.

05:44.160 --> 05:45.150
Come on.

05:45.280 --> 05:47.032
Everything.
What I have to do.

05:47.120 --> 05:49.555
That's good.
Now watch your head.

05:54.280 --> 05:56.271
(SIREN WAILING)

07:30.880 --> 07:31.995
Got one!

07:50.880 --> 07:52.109
Gunshot.

08:25.000 --> 08:26.434
LOU: Got another.

08:27.080 --> 08:28.991
Gerhardts, I'm thinking.

08:39.440 --> 08:41.431
No sign of Ed or Peggy.

08:46.680 --> 08:48.318
I'm calling a medic.

08:48.440 --> 08:51.080
Yeah, probably a good idea.

08:53.720 --> 08:55.757
This is just embarrassing.

08:56.480 --> 08:58.630
I'll get an APB out
on the Gerhardt boys,

08:58.760 --> 09:00.990
then see about starting
a hunt for Ed and Peggy.

09:01.080 --> 09:04.038
Don't tell Betsy I'm down.

09:04.120 --> 09:07.750
Yeah, she scares me more
than you, so I'm gonna call.

09:07.840 --> 09:08.955
Oh, you...

09:16.720 --> 09:17.994
(AMBULANCE DOORS CLOSE)

09:18.080 --> 09:19.434
(ENGINE STARTS)

09:23.040 --> 09:24.792
(SIRENS WAILING)

10:51.040 --> 10:52.713
(MUSIC PLAYING ON CAR STEREO)

11:00.480 --> 11:03.438
I've just been doing it
all wrong. Both of us.

11:03.520 --> 11:05.113
ED: We make a trade, hon,
is what I'm thinking.

11:05.200 --> 11:06.634
Wanting things, pretending
to be something we're not.

11:06.720 --> 11:08.518
Selling their man back
to them for freedom.

11:08.600 --> 11:10.477
It's like when
you're a kid and you

11:10.560 --> 11:12.039
need permission to
go to the washroom?

11:12.120 --> 11:14.350
And you raise your hand, and
wait for teacher to call on you,

11:14.440 --> 11:16.477
but meantime you
just have to go so bad.

11:16.600 --> 11:18.159
Should've looked at his
wallet. But you just go!

11:18.280 --> 11:20.237
Know exactly who
we're dealing with here.

11:20.320 --> 11:23.472
You just go! You
don't ask. You just go!

11:23.600 --> 11:27.833
Till then, hon, we stick to the
small roads, out-of-the-way motels,

11:27.920 --> 11:29.274
and we just...
We keep moving.

11:29.360 --> 11:30.509
A road trip.

11:30.600 --> 11:31.715
Wait, hold the phone.

11:31.800 --> 11:36.033
Uncle Grady's got that
hunting cabin outside Canistota.

11:36.120 --> 11:38.191
It's empty now.
We go there and hole up.

11:38.280 --> 11:42.717
See? We're moving now. Things
are flowing. Not trapped anymore.

11:43.760 --> 11:46.149
Well, I mean
that was our home.

11:46.240 --> 11:48.072
Yeah, but I mean,
energy wise.

11:48.160 --> 11:51.755
You know, I mean, you gotta
admit, we were stuck in the mud,

11:51.840 --> 11:55.117
emotionally, I mean.
And now, we're flying.

11:56.480 --> 11:59.040
We got a plan.
That's what matters.

11:59.120 --> 12:01.236
We got a plan for
how to get outta this.

12:01.320 --> 12:02.719
See it, then be it.

12:02.800 --> 12:04.552
That's from Lifespring.
Except... Except the cops.

12:04.640 --> 12:06.313
We gotta figure out...

12:06.680 --> 12:07.829
We're gonna
figure this out.

12:07.920 --> 12:11.038
Right now, I just gotta
keep us alive.

12:12.040 --> 12:14.475
You're doing it, hon.
We both are.

12:15.640 --> 12:17.278
We're actualized!

12:18.480 --> 12:19.515
(BOTH LAUGH)

12:43.760 --> 12:46.559
Oh, I like it.

12:46.640 --> 12:48.313
How come we've
never come here before?

12:48.520 --> 12:52.354
You said Uncle Grady smelled
like athlete's foot. Remember?

12:53.360 --> 12:54.509
PEGGY: Hon...

12:55.360 --> 12:57.590
What?
In case he gets feisty.

13:02.360 --> 13:03.350
(GRUNTS)

13:05.720 --> 13:06.710
(YELLS)

13:07.200 --> 13:08.873
(PEGGY EXCLAIMING)

13:10.200 --> 13:11.474
(GROANING)

13:16.920 --> 13:18.672
Good thinking, hon.

13:22.040 --> 13:23.030
(GROANING)

13:26.880 --> 13:28.279
My tongue.

13:28.720 --> 13:30.279
Bit off.
What?

13:31.400 --> 13:32.435
(SPITS)

13:32.520 --> 13:34.796
I bit my tongue half off.

13:36.320 --> 13:37.390
(DODD GRUNTS)

13:40.560 --> 13:43.313
You're dead,
in case you were wondering.

13:43.760 --> 13:44.909
You and your whore.

13:45.000 --> 13:46.513
Zip your lips.

13:46.920 --> 13:48.399
Dodd Gerhardt.

13:52.200 --> 13:54.760
I'm gonna have fun
taking her apart.

14:01.080 --> 14:02.070
(DODD GRUNTS)

14:02.160 --> 14:03.434
No.

14:10.920 --> 14:12.911
That's good, yeah?
Yeah.

14:14.600 --> 14:16.671
I saw a little convenience
store up the road.

14:16.760 --> 14:18.034
I'm gonna go
make the call.

14:18.120 --> 14:20.077
Oh, hon, there's
a phone in the bathroom.

14:20.440 --> 14:23.512
ED: Yeah, I'll use a pay
phone, make it untraceable.

14:23.720 --> 14:26.439
PEGGY: Oh, smart thinking,
Ed Blumquist.

14:26.520 --> 14:27.510
What are you gonna say?

14:27.880 --> 14:29.029
Well...

14:30.960 --> 14:34.032
You know, "If we
give him back to you,

14:34.120 --> 14:36.999
you gotta promise
we'll go unmolested."

14:38.960 --> 14:40.758
What if they say no?

14:41.960 --> 14:44.600
Well, then, I'll show them
which part's the flank steak.

14:48.560 --> 14:51.154
(COINS CLINKING)

14:55.960 --> 14:56.995
(PHONE DIALING)

15:10.040 --> 15:11.553
Yeah, it's...

15:13.200 --> 15:15.669
Is this the Gerhardt
headquarters?

15:17.680 --> 15:20.638
Good.
Well, this is the butcher.

15:21.840 --> 15:24.992
And I need to talk
to who's in charge.

15:26.960 --> 15:29.520
No, not your butcher,
"The Butcher."

15:30.280 --> 15:32.191
Yeah. From Luverne.

15:34.480 --> 15:36.835
So lemme talk to
who's in charge.

15:37.600 --> 15:38.999
I got Dodd.

15:40.600 --> 15:41.749
You heard me.

15:44.880 --> 15:47.838
Yeah. Yeah.

16:06.040 --> 16:08.839
What do you mean, a message?
Don't they...

16:08.920 --> 16:12.879
I mean, I got Dodd.
Did you tell 'em that?

16:13.880 --> 16:15.075
(SIGHS)

16:18.280 --> 16:21.079
Just tell them I'll
call them back, okay?

16:48.960 --> 16:50.075
(GRUNTS)

16:51.360 --> 16:53.431
Foot's on the other shoe now.

16:55.320 --> 16:56.390
Shut up.

16:56.800 --> 16:58.757
Oh, now, that's just rude.

16:59.000 --> 17:00.274
(GROANS)

17:01.520 --> 17:03.591
(GRUNTING) Come on,
for shit sake!

17:04.119 --> 17:07.511
Hey! Ed'll be back any
minute, so don't get any ideas.

17:13.640 --> 17:15.472
I got four daughters,
you know.

17:16.760 --> 17:18.397
I'm not a bad guy.

17:20.440 --> 17:22.795
You called me a whore.
I heard.

17:25.560 --> 17:28.279
I swear to Christ,
when I'm free,

17:28.400 --> 17:30.198
you're gonna see
the back of my hand.

17:31.760 --> 17:32.830
(ANGRY GRUNTING)

17:42.840 --> 17:46.071
PEGGY: We're gonna be
spending some time together.

17:46.160 --> 17:47.798
So you need to be civil.

17:48.800 --> 17:50.199
Go to hell.

17:55.400 --> 17:56.390
Ow!

17:56.480 --> 17:57.550
Bitch!

17:57.680 --> 17:58.670
(GROANS)

17:59.000 --> 18:00.115
Bitch!

18:00.480 --> 18:03.711
What did I just say?
Are you gonna be nice?

18:04.680 --> 18:07.718
Yeah, okay, okay.
All right! All right!

18:08.720 --> 18:09.710
Oh!

18:10.200 --> 18:11.349
Good.

18:12.320 --> 18:14.596
Now, I'm making beans.
You want some beans?

18:15.000 --> 18:16.070
No.

18:18.960 --> 18:20.314
No, what?

18:24.240 --> 18:25.719
No, thank you.

18:26.880 --> 18:27.995
That's better.

18:31.680 --> 18:35.196
I gotta say, this whole thing
has just been...

18:35.280 --> 18:39.592
And I mean, I'm sorry about your
brother. I am, but it was an accident.

18:40.000 --> 18:42.071
And this whole thing
has just been so...

18:42.160 --> 18:44.151
I mean,
I'm trying to stay positive.

18:44.240 --> 18:47.870
That's one thing, if you spend
any time with me you'll see.

18:47.960 --> 18:49.359
"Positive Peggy" is
what they call me.

18:49.880 --> 18:52.952
But this whole thing has
just been super hard on Ed.

18:53.040 --> 18:54.951
He's a little more
delicate, you know?

18:55.040 --> 18:58.158
I mean, he's a big guy
and all, but deep down...

18:58.280 --> 19:01.910
I mean, this whole thing has
just been really hard on him.

19:02.640 --> 19:04.677
And it's my fault.
I know.

19:06.400 --> 19:10.280
I mean,
I hit the guy,

19:11.920 --> 19:16.232
your brother,
and I'm sorry about that.

19:16.320 --> 19:17.435
I am,

19:18.560 --> 19:22.269
but he was stepping out
into the road.

19:24.240 --> 19:25.833
Didn't even look
where he was going.

19:25.920 --> 19:27.911
No, no. No.

19:28.040 --> 19:31.271
And so, Ed, you know,
all he did was clean it up.

19:32.960 --> 19:35.759
And then you sent those
other fellas, and...

19:35.840 --> 19:39.629
I mean, what were we
supposed to do? You know?

19:40.920 --> 19:43.992
So now I'm hoping,
we're both hoping,

19:45.840 --> 19:49.515
that we can just
smooth this all over now,

19:49.600 --> 19:52.274
and everything can
go back to normal.

19:55.280 --> 19:59.513
Oh, wait, now you said you
didn't want beans, didn't you?

20:00.640 --> 20:04.110
No, it's okay. They're good,
really. Good, good stuff.

20:04.800 --> 20:06.791
No. I mean,
I should've...

20:08.400 --> 20:13.236
Well... (SIGHS) With
everything that's been going on...

20:15.680 --> 20:18.320
And I mean,
here I am

20:18.400 --> 20:20.198
trying to actualize fully,
you know,

20:20.320 --> 20:22.789
and I mean,
that's no small thing.

20:23.000 --> 20:26.789
To review and reflect,
contextualize...

20:28.320 --> 20:31.153
Not just keep
making past mistakes.

20:32.000 --> 20:32.990
(CHUCKLING)

20:33.240 --> 20:35.709
Will you listen
to me nattering on. (CHUCKLES)

20:39.120 --> 20:40.997
Oh, hey, hon,
we're just...

20:41.120 --> 20:42.554
I made some beans.
You want some?

20:42.640 --> 20:44.313
ED: No, it's okay.

20:51.880 --> 20:53.473
What happened to him?

20:54.680 --> 20:57.877
Oh, well now, we don't
need to talk about that, do we?

20:58.440 --> 21:00.351
Water under the bridge.

21:03.760 --> 21:05.637
(SOFTLY) Hon, did you
stab the hostage?

21:05.720 --> 21:07.233
(WHISPERING) Yes. Yes.

21:07.320 --> 21:09.277
I mean, I had to teach him
some manners is all.

21:09.360 --> 21:12.591
If we're gonna be spending
time together. And him so angry.

21:12.680 --> 21:14.956
When we're the ones
who should be angry.

21:15.040 --> 21:18.590
I mean, when you get right down
to it, it's our shop that burned up.

21:18.680 --> 21:20.512
Help me. PEGGY: Our
house we had to leave behind.

21:20.600 --> 21:23.194
She's crazy.
Keep her away from me, man.

21:23.400 --> 21:25.038
ED: Hon...
Help me.

21:25.800 --> 21:27.473
Hon, hon.
Hmm?

21:28.400 --> 21:32.189
They're not gonna want him
back if we cut him up too much.

21:32.360 --> 21:33.714
Oh, I hardly
stuck him at all.

21:33.800 --> 21:34.870
I'm hurt real bad.

21:34.960 --> 21:35.950
Shut up.

21:36.040 --> 21:37.439
I think she punctured a lung.

21:37.520 --> 21:40.638
How'd it go with the family?
They gonna negotiate?

21:41.400 --> 21:43.471
Had to leave them
a message.

21:43.560 --> 21:45.631
Well, you said
we had him?

21:45.720 --> 21:48.519
Yeah, but it was just like
a flunky or something.

21:48.600 --> 21:50.398
So I said I'd call back.

21:50.480 --> 21:52.437
Okay, well,
maybe there's...

21:52.520 --> 21:54.989
Sounds like there's
a war going on up there.

21:55.080 --> 21:56.718
Maybe they're busy.

21:57.240 --> 21:59.629
Yeah, but, I mean, if he's
such an important guy...

21:59.720 --> 22:02.439
Now, hon, don't...

22:02.520 --> 22:04.511
Don't doubt yourself, Ed.

22:04.600 --> 22:08.070
That was my undoing.
See it, then be it, right?

22:09.280 --> 22:13.399
So just... Have some
beans and call back.

22:15.520 --> 22:18.080
They'll be home
next time for sure.

22:27.160 --> 22:28.434
Good?

22:30.960 --> 22:33.395
Hon, you gotta
stop stabbing him.

23:21.800 --> 23:23.473
(INSECTS BUZZING)

23:33.400 --> 23:35.118
(RADIO PLAYING)
(DOOR SLAMS)

23:42.520 --> 23:43.840
Water.

24:01.560 --> 24:03.437
Did you spit in this?

24:03.680 --> 24:04.875
What?

24:10.320 --> 24:13.278
Tequila.
Pour it in front of me.

24:24.840 --> 24:26.592
Here you go, chief.

24:33.360 --> 24:37.831
Looking for a couple. Red-headed
man and a blonde woman,

24:37.920 --> 24:39.797
driving a blue Lincoln.

24:39.880 --> 24:41.393
White couple?

24:43.120 --> 24:46.192
Didn't you guys try to start
your own country a while back?

24:47.040 --> 24:48.474
Wounded Knee?

24:49.600 --> 24:52.274
What happened there? Didn't you
feel like being Americans anymore?

24:53.640 --> 24:55.039
Not from there.

24:55.120 --> 24:57.031
BARTENDER: Yeah, see, well,

24:58.400 --> 25:00.676
I'm not sure I wanna
serve alcohol to a

25:00.760 --> 25:02.797
man who doesn't
want to be an American.

25:04.000 --> 25:05.593
How about a man did
three tours in Vietnam

25:05.680 --> 25:09.071
and got a Purple
Heart and a Bronze Star?

25:09.760 --> 25:11.114
Who? You?

25:19.240 --> 25:20.753
You're welcome.

25:22.120 --> 25:24.680
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

25:25.600 --> 25:26.590
(DOOR OPENS)

25:27.040 --> 25:29.680
(MEN TAUNTING)

25:29.760 --> 25:32.036
EARL: Where are you
going, Geronimo?

25:32.120 --> 25:34.031
You're gonna grab your
bow and arrow there?

25:34.120 --> 25:35.713
MAN 1: I don't think
his teepee's here.

25:35.800 --> 25:36.790
EARL: No. (LAUGHS)

25:38.280 --> 25:39.714
We're talking
to you, shitbird.

25:39.800 --> 25:41.552
Is that a teepee?

25:43.160 --> 25:45.197
MAN 2:
What are you doing, buddy?

25:45.280 --> 25:46.793
(EARL LAUGHING)

25:47.240 --> 25:48.833
Just wanted
a glass of water.

25:48.920 --> 25:51.560
EARL: Shitbird's thirsty.
Get a load of that.

25:51.640 --> 25:53.392
MAN 1: Is he crying, Earl?
I think he's crying.

25:54.760 --> 25:55.750
(YELLS)

25:55.840 --> 25:56.989
Fuck!

25:57.480 --> 25:59.869
MAN 2: Whoa, now, hold on a...
(YELLS)

26:01.520 --> 26:03.079
(BOTH GROANING)

26:17.160 --> 26:19.071
I called the cops.

26:19.440 --> 26:20.430
(CLATTERING)

26:23.720 --> 26:25.233
